To install the web service on your own computer you need:

- create a user & allocate a place for the code & the data writable by the user

- create jobs folder (note: it will eat up several dozen gigabytes during server operation)

- Edit config in wui.py to point to jobs folder (full path required)

- install python 2.7 with packages:
-- pip install numpy
-- pip install scipy
-- pip install python-bioformats sloth image tifffile flask

- wget -O static/jquery.js https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.2.1.min.js

- Add apache configuration like this (this example is for apache 2.4):

	WSGIDaemonProcess conredet user=conredet group=conredet
	WSGIScriptAlias /conredet .../conredet/wui_wsgi.py
	<Directory .../conredet>
		WSGIProcessGroup conredet
		WSGIApplicationGroup %{GLOBAL}
		WSGIPassAuthorization On
		WSGIScriptReloading On
		Require all granted
		Options +ExecCGI
	</Directory>

- Edit wui_wsgi.py, if you use virtualenv

- In a separate background process run ./wui_job.py -j /path/to/jobs/folder
